INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '3c910900-9611-40e1-93e3-4386eeab2fa7',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Flutter - Sharing Logic between Web and Mobile with a Monorepo Strategy$escape$,
  $escape$When building cross-platform apps with Flutter, you often need to share logic between your mobile and web implementations. To achieve this efficiently, consider using a monorepo strategy. Create a separate folder for shared code and define a pub package within it. Then, add the package to your mobile and web projects as dependencies. This way, you can manage shared logic in a central location, reducing code duplication and making maintenance easier. For example, create a pub package called `shared_logic` in a `lib/shared` folder:
```dart
// lib/shared/shared_logic/lib/shared_logic.dart
export 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';
default_value<T>(T Function() factory) => factory();
```$escape$,
  $escape$```dart
// lib/shared/shared_logic/lib/shared_logic.dart
export 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';
default_value<T>(T Function() factory) => factory();
// main.dart
import 'package:shared_logic/shared_logic.dart';
String defaultValue() => 'default value';
print(defaultValue());
```$escape$,
  $escape$dart$escape$,
